                        <sealDesc>
                            <summary>
                                <p>Three library seals of the kings of <placeName
                                        ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7001502">Awadh
                                        (Oude)</placeName>, intaglio-carved in nasta‘līq script in
                                    two stacked lines, impressed in vermillion ink.</p></summary>
                            <seal type="stamp" subtype="rectangle">
                                <p><label>1:</label> Rectangular seal of the library of <persName
                                        role="fmo" key="person_265857376">Nāṣir al-Dīn Ḥaydar Shāh
                                        (b. 1803, r. 1827–1837)</persName> dated <date
                                        calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when-custom="1244" notBefore="1828"
                                        notAfter="1829">1244 AH (1828–29 CE)</date>, inscribed with
                                    his title <addName type="epithet" key="person_265857376"
                                        >Sulaymān Jāh</addName>:</p>
                                <decoNote type="stamp" subtype="inscription"><p><quote xml:lang="fa"
                                            > خوش است مهر کتبخانه سلیمان جاه * بهر کتاب مزین چو نقش
                                            بسم الله، ١٢۴۴</quote></p>
                                    <p>
                                        <quote xml:lang="en"><hi rend="italic">Khvush ast muhur-i
                                                kitābkhānah-'i Sulaymān Jāh bahr-i kitāb; muzayyin
                                                chaw naqsh-i basmallah</hi>, <date
                                                calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when-custom="1244"
                                                notAfter="1829-07-02">1244 </date></quote> (<quote
                                            xml:lang="en">The seal of the library of Sulaymān Jāh is
                                            good; it embellishes the book like the design of a <hi
                                                rend="italic">basmallah</hi>, <date
                                                calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when-custom="1244"
                                                notBefore="1828-07-14" notAfter="1829-07-02"
                                                >1244</date></quote>).</p>
                                    <p><dimensions type="stamp" unit="mm">
                                            <height>17</height>
                                            <width>37</width>
                                        </dimensions></p></decoNote>
                            </seal>

                            <seal>
                                <p><label>2:</label> Rectangular seal surmounted by the royal emblem
                                    of Awadh, of <persName role="fmo"
                                        key="person_9680150325559110090006">Amjad ‘Alī Shāh (b.
                                        1801, r. 1842–1847)</persName> dated <date
                                        calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when-custom="1260"
                                        notBefore="1844-01-22" notAfter="1845-01-09">1260 AH
                                        (1844–45 CE):</date></p>
                                <decoNote type="stamp" subtype="inscription"><p><quote xml:lang="fa"
                                            >ناسخ هر مهر شد چون شد مزین بر کتاب * خاتم امجد علی شاه
                                            زمان عالیجناب، ١٢٦٠</quote></p>
                                    <p><quote xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc"><hi rend="italic">Nāsukh har
                                                muhur shud chun shud muzayyin bar kitāb; khātim-i
                                                Amjad ‘Alī Shāh zamān-i ‘Ālījanāb</hi>, <date
                                                calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when-custom="1260"
                                                notBefore="1844-01-22" notAfter="1845-01-09"
                                                >1260</date></quote> (<quote xml:lang="en">Every
                                            [prior] seal became cancelled since the book became
                                            embellished by the seal of Amjad ‘Alī Shāh in the era of
                                            his Sublime Majesty, <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari"
                                                when-custom="1260" notBefore="1844-01-22"
                                                notAfter="1845-01-09">1260</date></quote>).</p>
                                    <p><dimensions type="stamp" unit="mm">
                                            <height>53</height>
                                            <width>45</width>
                                        </dimensions></p></decoNote>
                            </seal>
                            <seal>
                                <p><label>3:</label> Rectangular seal surmounted by the royal emblem
                                    Awadh, of <persName role="fmo" key="person_305855167">Wājid ‘Alī
                                        Shāh (1822–1887), King of Awadh (r. 1847–1856)</persName>
                                    dated <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari" when-custom="1262"
                                        notBefore="1846" notAfter="1847">1262 AH (1846–47
                                    CE)</date>:</p>
                                <decoNote type="stamp" subtype="inscription"><p><quote xml:lang="fa"
                                            > خاتم واجد علی سلطان عالم بر کتاب * ثابت و پر نور بادا
                                            تا فروغ آفتاب، ١٢۶۲ </quote></p>
                                    <p><quote xml:lang="fa-Latn-x-lc"><hi rend="italic">Khātim-i
                                                Wājid ‘Alī, Sulṭān-i ‘Ālam bar kitāb, s̄abit va pur
                                                nūr bādā tā farūgh-i āftāb</hi>, 1262</quote> (<q
                                            xml:lang="en">The seal of Wājid ‘Alī, Sulṭān of the
                                            World, upon the book shall be permanent and as bright as
                                            sunlight, <date calendar="#Hijri-qamari"
                                                notBefore="1844-01-22" notAfter="1845-01-09"
                                                when-custom="1262">1262 AH [1847
                                        CE]</date></q>).</p>
                                    <p><dimensions type="stamp" unit="mm">
                                            <height>41</height>
                                            <width>26</width>
                                        </dimensions></p></decoNote>
                            </seal>
                        </sealDesc>
